            "text": [
              "<p></p><p><u><strong>Designing a Fair Game: Pondering Possible and Probable</strong></u></p><p>Santo and Tevy are designing another <em>Match, No Match</em> game with three coins. They take turns tossing three coins. They want the game to be fair. A <strong>fair game</strong> is a game in which all players have equal chances of winning.</p><p></p><p>If all three coins match, Santo wins. Otherwise, Tevy wins. Each player has won several times in the game. Tevy, however, seems to be winning more often. Santo thinks the game is unfair. </p><p></p><p>Tevy uses three coins to think about the outcomes. The set of all possible outcomes is called the <strong>sample space.</strong></p>"
            ]
          }
        },
